{
  "id": "def:370A",
  "kind": "definition",
  "number": "370A",
  "name": "Maintaining quadratic invariants",
  "is_helper": false,
  "chapter": 3,
  "section": "36",
  "subsection": "370",
  "subsection_title": "Maintaining quadratic invariants",
  "page": 297,
  "statement_text": "A Runge–Kutta method (A, b , c) is symplectic if\n\n                        M = diag(b)A + A diag(b) − bb\n\nis the zero matrix.\nThe property expressed by Definition 370A was first found by Cooper (1987)\nand, as a characteristic of symplectic methods, by Lasagni (1988), Sanz-Serna\n(1988) and Suris (1988).",
  "statement_latex": "\\begin{definition}\nA Runge--Kutta method $(A, b, c)$ is symplectic if\n\\[\nM = \\operatorname{diag}(b)A + A \\operatorname{diag}(b) - bb^{\\top}\n\\]\nis the zero matrix.\n\nThe property expressed by Definition~\\ref{def:370A} was first found by Cooper (1987) and, as a characteristic of symplectic methods, by Lasagni (1988), Sanz-Serna (1988) and Suris (1988).\n\\end{definition}",
  "proof_text": "",
  "proof_latex": "",
  "context_latex": "\\paragraph{Context}\nRunge--Kutta methods applied to ODEs with quadratic invariants; the matrix $M$ arises from analyzing preservation. A method is symplectic if $M=0$, conserving quadratic forms $y^{\\mathsf T}Q y$.\n\nVariables:\n\\begin{itemize}\n    \\item $A$: Runge--Kutta coefficient matrix\n    \\item $b$: Runge--Kutta weights vector\n    \\item $c$: Runge--Kutta nodes vector\n    \\item $M$: matrix $M=\\operatorname{diag}(b)A+A\\operatorname{diag}(b)-bb^{\\mathsf T}$\n    \\item $Q$: symmetric matrix defining invariant $y^{\\mathsf T}Q y$\n\\end{itemize}\n\nReferenced equation:\n\\begin{equation}\n    m_{ij}=b_i a_{ij}+b_j a_{ji}-b_i b_j \\tag{370a}\n\\end{equation}",
  "variables": [
    {
      "name": "A",
      "definition": "Runge-Kutta coefficient matrix"
    },
    {
      "name": "b",
      "definition": "Runge-Kutta weights vector"
    },
    {
      "name": "c",
      "definition": "Runge-Kutta nodes vector"
    },
    {
      "name": "M",
      "definition": "Matrix defined as M = diag(b)A + A diag(b) - bb^T"
    },
    {
      "name": "Q",
      "definition": "Symmetric matrix defining a quadratic invariant y^T Q y"
    }
  ],
  "equations": [
    {
      "tag": "370a",
      "content": "m_{ij} = b_i a_{ij} + b_j a_{ji} - b_i b_j"
    }
  ],
  "preamble": "The context involves Runge-Kutta methods applied to ODEs with quadratic invariants, where the matrix M arises from analyzing the preservation of these invariants. A method is symplectic if M is the zero matrix, ensuring conservation of quadratic forms like y^T Q y.",
  "introduces": [
    "symplectic"
  ],
